#, no-wrap
msgid "To make a context change survive to a `restorecon`, you have to modify the default file contexts with the `semanage fcontext` command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:351
#, no-wrap
msgid "semanage fcontext -a options file\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:358
#, no-wrap
msgid "    If you are performing a context switch for a folder that is not standard for the system, creating the rule and then applying the context is a good practice as in the example below!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:361
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo semanage fcontext -a -t httpd_sys_content_t \"/data/websites(/.*)?\"\n"
"$ sudo restorecon -vR /data/websites/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:366
#, no-wrap
msgid "`audit2why` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `audit2why` command indicates the cause of a SELinux rejection:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "audit2why [-vw]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example to get the cause of the last rejection by SELinux:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:376
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:418
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo cat /var/log/audit/audit.log | grep AVC | grep denied | tail -1 | audit2why\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:384
#, no-wrap
msgid "| Options | Observations                                                                                         |\n"
"|---------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-v`    | Switch into verbose mode                                                                             |\n"
"| `-w`    | Translates the cause of a rejection by SELinux and proposes a solution to remedy it (default option) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:385
#, no-wrap
msgid "Going further with SELinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `audit2allow` command creates a module to allow a SELinux action (when no module exists) from a line in an \"audit\" file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:389
#, no-wrap
msgid "audit2allow [-mM]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:395
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo cat /var/log/audit/audit.log | grep AVC | grep denied | tail -1 | audit2allow -M mylocalmodule\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:403
#, no-wrap
msgid "| Options | Observations                                       |\n"
"|---------|----------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-m`    | Just create the module (`*.te`)                    |\n"
"| `-M`    | Create the module, compile and package it (`*.pp`) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:404
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example of configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:407
#, no-wrap
msgid "After the execution of a command, the system gives you back the command prompt but the expected result is not visible: no error message on the screen.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Step 1**: Read the log file knowing that the message we are interested in is of type AVC (SELinux), refused (denied) and the most recent one (therefore the last one).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:410
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo cat /var/log/audit/audit.log | grep AVC | grep denied | tail -1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:415
#, no-wrap
msgid "The message is correctly isolated but is of no help to us.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:417
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Step 2**: Read the isolated message with the `audit2why` command to get a more explicit message that may contain the solution to our problem (typically a boolean to be set).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:423
#, no-wrap
msgid "There are two cases: either we can place a context or fill in a boolean, or we must go to step 3 to create our own context.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:425
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Step 3**: Create your own module.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:426
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo cat /var/log/audit/audit.log | grep AVC | grep denied | tail -1 | audit2allow -M mylocalmodule\n"
"Generating type enforcement: mylocalmodule.te\n"
"Compiling policy: checkmodule -M -m -o mylocalmodule.mod mylocalmodule.te\n"
"Building package: semodule_package -o mylocalmodule.pp -m mylocalmodule.mod\n\n"
"$ sudo semodule -i mylocalmodule.pp\n"
msgstr ""

